DEPRECATED: This KM has been deprecated and may be removed without prior notice in future ODI versions. Please use MTI functionality of ODI mappings.
COMPONENT NAME: IKM Oracle Multi Table Insert
AUTHOR: Oracle
DESCRIPTION: - Integrates data from one source into one to many Oracle target tables in append mode, using a multi-table insert statement (MTI).
REQUIREMENTS: - Oracle Database 9iR1 or above - See BASIC CONFIGURATION section
BASIC CONFIGURATION - This IKM must be used in integration interfaces that are sequenced in a Package: - The first interface of the Package must have a temporary target and the KM option DEFINE_QUERY set to YES. This first interface defines the structure of the SELECT clause of the multi-table insert statement (that is the source flow). - Subsequent integration interfaces must source from this temporary datastore and have the KM option IS_TARGET_TABLE set to YES. - The last interface of the Package must have the KM option EXECUTE set to YES in order to run the multi-table insert statement. - Do not set "Use Temporary Interface as Derived Table(Sub-Select)" set to true on any of the interfaces. - If large amounts of data are appended, consider to set the KM option OPTIMIZER_HINT to /*+ APPEND */.
OPTIONS (Refer to the Option descriptions for more information on each option) - DEFINE_QUERY: Set to Yes if this interface describes the source query (SELECT clause of the statement). This interface must have a temporary target. - IS_TARGET_TABLE: Set to Yes this interface using the source query to load one of the target tables. This interface must source from an interface with a temporary target using this IKM and having the KM option DEFINE_QUERY set to YES. - EXECUTE: Set to Yes for the last interface in the Package. This interface will run the multi-table insert statement. - COMMIT: Commit transaction. This applies only to the last interface in the Package. - TRUNCATE: Set to Yes to truncate this interface target table. - CREATE_TARG_TABLE: Create target table? May only be used on target interfaces, but not on source interfaces (defining the source data). - OPTIMIZER_HINT: Hint for the multi-table insert statement.
RESTRICTIONS: - This KM can only be used in integration interfaces that are part of a Package. - All source and target datastores need to reside on same data server. - Staging area must be set to target on all interfaces. - Journalized source data is not supported. - Temporary indexes are not supported. - Flow/static control is not supported. - The TRUNCATE option cannot work, if the target table is referenced by another table (foreign key).

Prepare the Multi-Table Insert Query without executing anything on the database. Set this option to yes if this interface describes the source query (SELECT clause of the statement). This interface must have a temporary target.
Is this table one of the targets?
Set this option to yes, if this interface loads one of the targets of the multi-insert statement. This interface must source from the interface with DEFINE_QUERY=YES.
Set to yes for the last interface in the chain of interfaces loading the targets. This interface will run the multi-insert statement.
Commit all data inserted in the target datastores. This only applies to the last interface in the chain of interfaces loading the targets
Check this option, if you wish to truncate the target datastore.
Check this option, if you wish to create the target table May only be used on target interfaces, but not on source interfaces (defining the source data).

Use this option to specify the hint to be used while loading the target tables.
E.g. /*+ APPEND */ for appending to target tables for better performance, but potentially increased tablespace usage

<%
StringBuffer Query = new StringBuffer();
String nl = "" + (char)10;

// Iterate over all DataSets
for (int i=0; i < odiRef.getDataSetCount(); i++) {
	Query.append( odiRef.getDataSet(i, "Operator") +nl );
	Query.append( "select	" + odiRef.getPop("DISTINCT_ROWS") +nl);
	Query.append( "	" + odiRef.getColList(i, "", "[EXPRESSION] [COL_NAME]", ",\n\t", "", "INS and REW") +nl);
	Query.append( "from	" + odiRef.getFrom(i) +nl); 
	if (odiRef.getDataSet(i, "HAS_JRN").equals("1")) { 
		Query.append( "where	JRN_FLAG <> 'D' " +nl);
	} else { 
		Query.append( "where	(1=1) " +nl);
	}; 
	Query.append( odiRef.getJoin(i) +nl);
	Query.append( odiRef.getFilter(i) +nl);
	Query.append( odiRef.getJrnFilter(i) +nl);
	Query.append( odiRef.getGrpBy(i) +nl);
	Query.append( odiRef.getHaving(i) +nl);
}; // DataSet loop

Vector Targets = new Vector();
%>

<%
// Does this interface have more than one source data store?
if ( odiRef.getSrcTablesList("", "X", "","").length() != 1 ) {
	%>raise OdiKMException("ODIKM-ORA-IKM-10000", "ODIKM-ORA-IKM-10000: This IKM only supports exactly one source data store")<%
} else

// Has the source already been defined?
if ( Targets == void ) {
	%>raise OdiKMException("ODIKM-ORA-IKM-10001", "ODIKM-ORA-IKM-10001: Defining a target, but no source has been defined, yet. Please define source first.")<%
} else {

// regularExpression to locate aliases
String searchExpr = 	odiRef.getSrcTablesList("",
			""+(char)92+(char)92+"b"+	// Word boundary
			(char)92+(char)92+"Q"+		// Begin quotation
			"[POP_TAB_ALIAS]."+
			(char)92+(char)92+"E"+		// End quotation
			(char)92+(char)92+"b",		// Word bundary
		"",""); 	

String[] Target={
	odiRef.getTable("L","TARG_NAME","A"),
	odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ", ", "", "INS and REW"),
	// Remove all aliases from expressions
	odiRef.getColList("", "[EXPRESSION]", ", ", "", "INS and REW").replaceAll(searchExpr,""),
	// Remove all aliases from filters
	odiRef.getFilter().replaceAll(searchExpr, "")
	};

Targets.add(Target);

} // end of else - Error conditions

%>
# Adding target table

<% 
// Has the source already been defined?
if ( Query == void ) {
                           odiRef.getLogger().log(java.util.logging.Level.SEVERE,  "ODIKM-ORA-IKM-10002", "Trying to execute INSERT ALL, but no source has been defined, yet. Please define source first.");
	out.print( "Error: Trying to execute INSERT ALL, but no source has been defined, yet. Please define source first." );
} else 

// Have any targets been already defined?
if ( Targets == void || Targets.size()==0 ) {
                           odiRef.getLogger().log(java.util.logging.Level.SEVERE,  "ODIKM-ORA-IKM-10003", "Trying to execute INSERT ALL, but targets have not been defined, yet. Please define at least one target first." );
	out.print( "Error: Trying to execute INSERT ALL, but targets have not been defined, yet. Please define at least one target first." );
} else {

%>insert <%=odiRef.getOption("OPTIMIZER_HINT")%> all 
<%for (int i=0; i< Targets.size(); i++){%>
when 1=1 <%=((String[])Targets.get(i))[3]%> then
into <%=((String[])Targets.get(i))[0]%>
(<%=((String[])Targets.get(i))[1]%>)
values
(<%=((String[])Targets.get(i))[2]%>)
<%}%>
<%=Query%>

<%
unset( "Query" );
unset( "Targets" );
%>
<% };%>
